<body> Social media has grown exponentially in the last few years, and due to its rise, advertising has shifted. Influencers are now one of the best ways for brands to push products. The impact of the influencer economy seems to be aimed at teen girls and young women who use social media frequently. Seeing a perfect version of the lives of peers can trigger negative emotions such as envy, anxiety or depression. In the same way that parasocial relationships can be built through social media, envy can be built through comparison to influencers that are viewed as peers with an attainable lifestyle. Negative emotions that arise from social media usage cause consumers to make purchases


